===Etymology 1===
Originally a [[Sussex]] habitational name, the word "[[leag]]" or "[[ley]]" meaning [[field]] in [[Anglo-Saxon]]. Hence, {{af|en|bent|t1=bent-grass|[[leigh]]/[[lea]]|t2=meadow, field|nocat=1}}, see also {{mention|en|Bentham}}.

